---
import Layout from '../layouts/Layout.astro';

const title = "Wolf Appliance Repair Los Angeles | Same Day Service";
const description = "Expert Wolf appliance repair in Los Angeles. Certified technicians for ranges, ovens, cooktops, steam ovens, ventilation & outdoor grills. Same-day service, OEM parts, 90-day warranty. Call (626) 376-4458.";
const phone = "(626) 376-4458";
const phoneRaw = "6263764458";
---

<Layout title={title} description={description}>

<script type="application/ld+json">
{
  "@context": "https://schema.org",
  "@type": "HomeAndConstructionBusiness",
  "name": "Same Day Appliance Repair — Wolf Specialist",
  "url": "https://samedayappliance.repair/brand-wolf-appliance-repair/",
  "telephone": "+16263764458",
  "address": {
    "@type": "PostalAddress",
    "addressLocality": "Los Angeles",
    "addressRegion": "CA",
    "postalCode": "90001",
    "addressCountry": "US"
  },
  "areaServed": ["Los Angeles County", "Orange County", "Ventura County"],
  "priceRange": "$$",
  "openingHours": "Mo-Sa 08:00-20:00",
  "hasOfferCatalog": {
    "@type": "OfferCatalog",
    "name": "Wolf Repair Services",
    "itemListElement": [
      {"@type":"Offer","itemOffered":{"@type":"Service","name":"Wolf Range Repair"}},
      {"@type":"Offer","itemOffered":{"@type":"Service","name":"Wolf Oven Repair"}},
      {"@type":"Offer","itemOffered":{"@type":"Service","name":"Wolf Cooktop Repair"}},
      {"@type":"Offer","itemOffered":{"@type":"Service","name":"Wolf Steam Oven Repair"}},
      {"@type":"Offer","itemOffered":{"@type":"Service","name":"Wolf Ventilation Repair"}},
      {"@type":"Offer","itemOffered":{"@type":"Service","name":"Wolf Outdoor Grill Repair"}}
    ]
  }
}
</script>

<script type="application/ld+json">
{
  "@context": "https://schema.org",
  "@type": "FAQPage",
  "mainEntity": [
    {
      "@type": "Question",
      "name": "How much does Wolf appliance repair cost in Los Angeles?",
      "acceptedAnswer": {
        "@type": "Answer",
        "text": "Most Wolf repairs run $195–$680. Igniter replacement or temperature sensor calibration is on the lower end. Control board or sealed-system convection work runs higher. Diagnostic fee is $89, waived when you proceed. Written flat-rate estimate before work begins."
      }
    },
    {
      "@type": "Question",
      "name": "Do you repair Wolf outdoor grills in Los Angeles?",
      "acceptedAnswer": {
        "@type": "Answer",
        "text": "Yes. We service Wolf outdoor grills and outdoor kitchen equipment — burner systems, ignition, temperature control, and weatherproofing. LA's coastal salt air and Santa Ana wind conditions accelerate outdoor grill wear significantly. We stock OEM Wolf outdoor components and service all models."
      }
    },
    {
      "@type": "Question",
      "name": "Can you service both Wolf and Sub-Zero in the same visit?",
      "acceptedAnswer": {
        "@type": "Answer",
        "text": "Yes. Wolf and Sub-Zero are part of the same Sub-Zero Group, and many LA kitchens have both. We service the complete kitchen suite in a single visit — Wolf range, Sub-Zero refrigerator, and Cove dishwasher if needed. One call, one visit, one technician who knows all three brands."
      }
    },
    {
      "@type": "Question",
      "name": "Why does my Wolf oven temperature fluctuate?",
      "acceptedAnswer": {
        "@type": "Answer",
        "text": "Most Wolf oven temperature swings trace back to three causes: a worn door gasket allowing heat loss, a failing temperature sensor (probe), or a convection fan running at reduced speed. We test all three before recommending parts. The door gasket is the most common cause and the least expensive fix."
      }
    },
    {
      "@type": "Question",
      "name": "How often should Wolf appliances be serviced in Los Angeles?",
      "acceptedAnswer": {
        "@type": "Answer",
        "text": "Annually for ranges and cooktops used regularly — burner calibration, igniter inspection, valve check, oven temperature verification. Wolf ventilation hoods need duct cleaning every 6–12 months depending on cooking volume. Outdoor grills need weatherproofing inspection each season. LA's coastal humidity and Santa Ana conditions accelerate wear on ignition systems and external components."
      }
    },
    {
      "@type": "Question",
      "name": "Do you service Wolf ventilation hoods and range hoods?",
      "acceptedAnswer": {
        "@type": "Answer",
        "text": "Yes. Wolf ventilation hoods — wall, island, and integrated — are a dedicated service area. Common issues: blower motor failure, speed selector fault, lighting, and duct restriction. A blocked Wolf vent hood not only fails to clear smoke and steam but can back-pressure into the range and affect burner performance."
      }
    }
  ]
}
</script>

<style>
  :root {
    --red: #C8102E;
    --black: #0a0a0a;
    --gray: #f5f5f5;
    --border: #e2e2e2;
    --text: #1a1a1a;
    --muted: #6b6b6b;
  }
  * { box-sizing: border-box; margin: 0; padding: 0; }
  body { font-family: 'Barlow', 'Inter', system-ui, sans-serif; color: var(--text); }

  .top-bar { background: var(--red); padding: 8px 24px; display: flex; justify-content: space-between; align-items: center; font-size: 13px; color: #fff; }
  .top-bar a { color: #fff; text-decoration: none; font-weight: 700; }

  .hero { background: var(--black); padding: 72px 24px 64px; color: #fff; }
  .hero-inner { max-width: 1100px; margin: 0 auto; display: grid; grid-template-columns: 1fr 420px; gap: 48px; align-items: center; }
  .hero-eyebrow { font-size: 11px; font-weight: 700; letter-spacing: 0.15em; text-transform: uppercase; color: var(--red); margin-bottom: 16px; }
  .hero-title { font-size: clamp(32px, 5vw, 52px); font-weight: 900; line-height: 1.05; text-transform: uppercase; letter-spacing: -0.02em; margin-bottom: 20px; }
  .hero-title span { color: var(--red); }
  .hero-sub { font-size: 17px; line-height: 1.6; color: #aaa; margin-bottom: 32px; max-width: 540px; }
  .hero-cta-group { display: flex; gap: 16px; flex-wrap: wrap; }
  .btn-primary { display: inline-block; background: var(--red); color: #fff; padding: 14px 28px; font-size: 15px; font-weight: 700; text-decoration: none; letter-spacing: 0.04em; text-transform: uppercase; }
  .btn-secondary { display: inline-block; border: 1px solid #555; color: #ccc; padding: 14px 28px; font-size: 15px; font-weight: 600; text-decoration: none; letter-spacing: 0.04em; text-transform: uppercase; }
  .hero-badge-grid { display: grid; grid-template-columns: 1fr 1fr; gap: 12px; }
  .hero-badge { background: #161616; border: 1px solid #2a2a2a; padding: 16px 18px; }
  .badge-num { font-size: 28px; font-weight: 900; color: var(--red); line-height: 1; margin-bottom: 4px; }
  .badge-label { font-size: 12px; color: #888; text-transform: uppercase; letter-spacing: 0.08em; }

  .trust-bar { background: var(--red); padding: 14px 24px; }
  .trust-bar-inner { max-width: 1100px; margin: 0 auto; display: flex; justify-content: space-between; flex-wrap: wrap; gap: 8px; }
  .trust-item { color: #fff; font-size: 13px; font-weight: 600; letter-spacing: 0.04em; text-transform: uppercase; }
  .trust-item::before { content: "✓ "; }

  .section { padding: 64px 24px; }
  .section-gray { background: var(--gray); }
  .section-black { background: var(--black); color: #fff; }
  .section-inner { max-width: 1100px; margin: 0 auto; }
  .section-num { font-size: 11px; font-weight: 700; letter-spacing: 0.15em; text-transform: uppercase; color: var(--red); margin-bottom: 8px; }
  .section-title { font-size: clamp(24px, 3.5vw, 36px); font-weight: 900; text-transform: uppercase; letter-spacing: -0.01em; margin-bottom: 20px; }
  .section-black .section-title { color: #fff; }
  .section-lead { font-size: 17px; line-height: 1.7; color: var(--muted); max-width: 760px; margin-bottom: 40px; }
  .section-black .section-lead { color: #999; }

  .services-grid { display: grid; grid-template-columns: repeat(auto-fill, minmax(300px, 1fr)); gap: 1px; background: var(--border); border: 1px solid var(--border); }
  .service-card { background: #fff; padding: 28px 24px; }
  .service-icon { font-size: 28px; margin-bottom: 12px; }
  .service-name { font-size: 16px; font-weight: 800; text-transform: uppercase; letter-spacing: 0.04em; margin-bottom: 10px; color: var(--text); }
  .service-desc { font-size: 14px; line-height: 1.65; color: var(--muted); margin-bottom: 12px; }
  .service-issues { font-size: 12px; color: var(--red); font-weight: 600; text-transform: uppercase; letter-spacing: 0.06em; }

  .tip-block { border-left: 3px solid var(--red); background: #fff8f8; padding: 18px 20px; margin: 32px 0; max-width: 760px; }
  .tip-label { font-size: 10px; font-weight: 800; text-transform: uppercase; letter-spacing: 0.15em; color: var(--red); margin-bottom: 6px; }
  .tip-text { font-size: 14px; line-height: 1.65; color: var(--text); }
  .tip-outdoor { border-color: #2a7a2a; background: #f0fff4; }
  .tip-outdoor .tip-label { color: #2a7a2a; }
  .tip-blue { border-color: #3a7bd5; background: #f0f7ff; }
  .tip-blue .tip-label { color: #3a7bd5; }

  .features-2col { display: grid; grid-template-columns: 1fr 1fr; gap: 48px; align-items: start; }
  .features-list { list-style: none; }
  .features-list li { padding: 14px 0; border-bottom: 1px solid #2a2a2a; font-size: 15px; color: #ccc; display: flex; gap: 12px; }
  .features-list li::before { content: "→"; color: var(--red); flex-shrink: 0; }

  .suite-grid { display: grid; grid-template-columns: repeat(3, 1fr); gap: 1px; background: #2a2a2a; border: 1px solid #2a2a2a; margin-top: 32px; }
  .suite-card { background: #161616; padding: 24px 20px; text-align: center; }
  .suite-brand { font-size: 18px; font-weight: 900; text-transform: uppercase; letter-spacing: 0.08em; color: #fff; margin-bottom: 6px; }
  .suite-role { font-size: 12px; color: var(--red); text-transform: uppercase; letter-spacing: 0.1em; font-weight: 700; margin-bottom: 10px; }
  .suite-desc { font-size: 13px; color: #888; line-height: 1.5; }
  .suite-card.featured { background: #1a0a0a; }
  .suite-card.featured .suite-brand { color: var(--red); }

  .problems-grid { display: grid; grid-template-columns: repeat(auto-fill, minmax(260px, 1fr)); gap: 16px; margin-top: 32px; }
  .problem-card { border: 1px solid var(--border); background: #fff; padding: 20px; }
  .problem-title { font-size: 14px; font-weight: 800; text-transform: uppercase; letter-spacing: 0.05em; margin-bottom: 8px; color: var(--text); }
  .problem-cause { font-size: 13px; color: var(--muted); line-height: 1.6; margin-bottom: 10px; }
  .problem-tag { display: inline-block; font-size: 11px; font-weight: 700; text-transform: uppercase; letter-spacing: 0.08em; padding: 3px 8px; color: #fff; }
  .tag-common { background: var(--red); }
  .tag-la { background: #2a5ea5; }
  .tag-outdoor { background: #2a7a2a; }

  .pricing-table { width: 100%; border-collapse: collapse; margin-top: 24px; }
  .pricing-table th { background: var(--text); color: #fff; text-align: left; padding: 12px 16px; font-size: 12px; text-transform: uppercase; letter-spacing: 0.08em; }
  .pricing-table td { padding: 14px 16px; border-bottom: 1px solid var(--border); font-size: 14px; }
  .pricing-table tr:last-child td { border-bottom: none; }
  .pricing-table tr:nth-child(even) td { background: var(--gray); }
  .price-range { font-weight: 700; color: var(--red); }

  .why-grid { display: grid; grid-template-columns: repeat(auto-fill, minmax(220px, 1fr)); gap: 24px; margin-top: 32px; }
  .why-card { border-left: 3px solid var(--red); padding: 20px; background: #fff; }
  .why-icon { font-size: 24px; margin-bottom: 10px; }
  .why-title { font-size: 14px; font-weight: 800; text-transform: uppercase; letter-spacing: 0.05em; margin-bottom: 8px; }
  .why-desc { font-size: 13px; color: var(--muted); line-height: 1.6; }

  .reviews-grid { display: grid; grid-template-columns: repeat(auto-fill, minmax(300px, 1fr)); gap: 20px; margin-top: 32px; }
  .review-card { background: #fff; border: 1px solid var(--border); padding: 24px; }
  .review-stars { color: var(--red); font-size: 18px; margin-bottom: 10px; }
  .review-text { font-size: 14px; line-height: 1.7; color: var(--text); margin-bottom: 14px; }
  .review-author { font-size: 12px; font-weight: 700; text-transform: uppercase; color: var(--muted); }

  .repairs-grid { display: grid; grid-template-columns: repeat(auto-fill, minmax(300px, 1fr)); gap: 1px; background: var(--border); border: 1px solid var(--border); margin-top: 32px; }
  .repair-item { background: #fff; padding: 24px; }
  .repair-appliance { font-size: 11px; font-weight: 700; text-transform: uppercase; letter-spacing: 0.1em; color: var(--red); margin-bottom: 6px; }
  .repair-issue { font-size: 15px; font-weight: 800; color: var(--text); margin-bottom: 8px; }
  .repair-detail { font-size: 13px; color: var(--muted); line-height: 1.6; }
  .repair-meta { margin-top: 12px; font-size: 12px; font-weight: 600; color: #aaa; text-transform: uppercase; letter-spacing: 0.06em; }

  .faq-list { margin-top: 32px; }
  .faq-item { border-bottom: 1px solid var(--border); padding: 20px 0; }
  .faq-q { font-size: 16px; font-weight: 800; color: var(--text); margin-bottom: 10px; }
  .faq-a { font-size: 14px; line-height: 1.7; color: var(--muted); max-width: 760px; }

  .nearby-grid { display: flex; flex-wrap: wrap; gap: 8px; margin-top: 20px; }
  .nearby-chip { background: var(--gray); border: 1px solid var(--border); padding: 8px 14px; font-size: 13px; color: var(--muted); text-decoration: none; font-weight: 600; }
  .nearby-chip:hover { border-color: var(--red); color: var(--red); }

  .bottom-cta { background: var(--black); padding: 72px 24px; text-align: center; color: #fff; }
  .bottom-cta-title { font-size: clamp(28px, 4vw, 44px); font-weight: 900; text-transform: uppercase; letter-spacing: -0.01em; margin-bottom: 12px; }
  .bottom-cta-title span { color: var(--red); }
  .bottom-cta-sub { font-size: 17px; color: #888; margin-bottom: 32px; }
  .cta-phone-large { display: inline-block; font-size: clamp(28px, 4vw, 42px); font-weight: 900; color: #fff; text-decoration: none; letter-spacing: -0.01em; margin-bottom: 24px; border-bottom: 2px solid var(--red); padding-bottom: 4px; }

  @media (max-width: 768px) {
    .hero-inner { grid-template-columns: 1fr; }
    .hero-badge-grid { grid-template-columns: 1fr 1fr; }
    .features-2col { grid-template-columns: 1fr; }
    .suite-grid { grid-template-columns: 1fr; }
    .trust-bar-inner { flex-direction: column; gap: 6px; }
  }
</style>

<!-- TOP BAR -->
<div class="top-bar">
  <span>Mon–Sat 8am–8pm · Los Angeles &amp; Southern California</span>
  <a href={`tel:${phoneRaw}`}>{phone}</a>
</div>

<!-- HERO -->
<section class="hero">
  <div class="hero-inner">
    <div>
      <div class="hero-eyebrow">Wolf Appliance Repair — Los Angeles</div>
      <h1 class="hero-title">
        Wolf Repair.<br/>
        <span>The Whole</span><br/>
        Kitchen Suite.
      </h1>
      <p class="hero-sub">
        Wolf ranges, ovens, cooktops, steam ovens, ventilation hoods, and outdoor grills — we service the complete lineup, same day. Wolf belongs to Sub-Zero Group, and so does our expertise: one call covers your entire kitchen, indoor and out.
      </p>
      <div class="hero-cta-group">
        <a href={`tel:${phoneRaw}`} class="btn-primary">Call {phone}</a>
        <a href="/book/" class="btn-secondary">Book Online</a>
      </div>
    </div>
    <div class="hero-badge-grid">
      <div class="hero-badge">
        <div class="badge-num">Same</div>
        <div class="badge-label">Day Service</div>
      </div>
      <div class="hero-badge">
        <div class="badge-num">OEM</div>
        <div class="badge-label">Wolf Parts</div>
      </div>
      <div class="hero-badge">
        <div class="badge-num">90-Day</div>
        <div class="badge-label">Warranty</div>
      </div>
      <div class="hero-badge">
        <div class="badge-num">$89</div>
        <div class="badge-label">Diagnostic Fee</div>
      </div>
    </div>
  </div>
</section>

<!-- TRUST BAR -->
<div class="trust-bar">
  <div class="trust-bar-inner">
    <span class="trust-item">Licensed &amp; Insured · CSLB #1138898</span>
    <span class="trust-item">Wolf + Sub-Zero + Cove Suite Service</span>
    <span class="trust-item">Genuine Wolf OEM Parts</span>
    <span class="trust-item">Outdoor Grill Specialists</span>
    <span class="trust-item">Flat-Rate Written Estimate</span>
  </div>
</div>

<!-- 01 — ABOUT WOLF -->
<section class="section">
  <div class="section-inner">
    <div class="section-num">01 — About Wolf</div>
    <h2 class="section-title">Professional Heat, Built for Home Kitchens</h2>
    <p class="section-lead">
      Wolf has been making professional-grade cooking equipment since 1934 — originally for commercial kitchens, then adapting that engineering for residential use. The dual-stack burner that delivers both a 15,000 BTU high flame and a 500 BTU simmer without swapping parts. The infrared broiler that reaches 1,850°F. The convection system with a variable-speed fan that adjusts automatically to what's in the oven. This is equipment designed to be used hard, every day, for decades.
    </p>
    <p class="section-lead">
      In 2000, Wolf was acquired by Sub-Zero — now operating as Sub-Zero Group alongside Sub-Zero refrigeration and Cove dishwashers. The practical result for homeowners: many LA kitchens have the full suite. We service all three brands, often in a single visit. One technician who knows the Wolf range, the Sub-Zero column refrigerator, and the Cove dishwasher — not three separate service calls.
    </p>

    <div class="tip-block tip-blue">
      <div class="tip-label">🌊 LA Climate and Wolf Cooking Equipment</div>
      <div class="tip-text">Coastal humidity (Malibu, Pacific Palisades, Santa Monica) accelerates corrosion on Wolf igniter ceramics, valve stems, and outdoor grill components. Santa Ana conditions drive fine dust into Wolf oven convection systems and range hoods faster than in most markets. Annual service is particularly worthwhile in coastal and hilltop LA properties — we find problems before they become failures.</div>
    </div>
  </div>
</section>

<!-- 02 — SERVICES -->
<section class="section section-gray">
  <div class="section-inner">
    <div class="section-num">02 — Services</div>
    <h2 class="section-title">Every Wolf Appliance We Service</h2>
    <p class="section-lead">Same-day availability across Los Angeles County. We carry OEM Wolf parts for all current and legacy models.</p>

    <div class="services-grid">
      <div class="service-card">
        <div class="service-icon">🔥</div>
        <div class="service-name">Range Repair</div>
        <div class="service-desc">All Wolf range configurations — gas, dual-fuel, and induction. The dual-stack burner design means igniter failures are model-specific and require OEM parts; generic igniters don't reach the correct geometry for the dual-flame stack. We carry bake, broil, and spark igniters for current Wolf range models.</div>
        <div class="service-issues">Common: dual-stack igniter failure · burner won't light · oven temperature off · dual-fuel ignition · control board · door gasket worn · self-clean lock · bake element</div>
      </div>

      <div class="service-card">
        <div class="service-icon">🌡️</div>
        <div class="service-name">Wall Oven Repair</div>
        <div class="service-desc">Wolf M Series and E Series wall ovens — single, double, and combination units. The variable-speed convection fan is Wolf's signature — when it starts running at a fixed speed instead of adjusting dynamically, baking results become unpredictable. We test and replace the fan motor and speed controller.</div>
        <div class="service-issues">Common: temperature fluctuation · convection fan failure · door gasket worn · heating element · temperature sensor · control board · door spring · self-clean fault</div>
      </div>

      <div class="service-card">
        <div class="service-icon">⚡</div>
        <div class="service-name">Cooktop Repair</div>
        <div class="service-desc">Gas, electric, induction, and transition cooktops. Wolf induction cooktops use a different power architecture than most — the inverter design delivers faster response but fails differently than standard induction. We diagnose by zone, not by swapping the full board.</div>
        <div class="service-issues">Common: igniter not sparking · burner won't light · induction zone dead · flame adjustment · surface element failure · control board · downdraft motor</div>
      </div>

      <div class="service-card">
        <div class="service-icon">💨</div>
        <div class="service-name">Ventilation &amp; Hood Repair</div>
        <div class="service-desc">Wolf wall hoods, island hoods, and integrated ventilation systems. A failed Wolf hood motor isn't just an inconvenience — back-pressure from a blocked vent system can affect burner combustion on the range below. We service the blower motor, speed selector, lighting, and duct connection.</div>
        <div class="service-issues">Common: blower motor failure · speed selector fault · lighting out · excessive noise · duct restriction · grease filter cleaning · back-pressure on range</div>
      </div>

      <div class="service-card">
        <div class="service-icon">☁️</div>
        <div class="service-name">Steam Oven Repair</div>
        <div class="service-desc">Wolf convection steam ovens (CSO series) and speed ovens. LA hard water scales the steam generator faster than Wolf's standard maintenance interval assumes — we descale, replace the water inlet valve if seized, and set the descaling reminder to match your actual water supply hardness.</div>
        <div class="service-issues">Common: steam not generating · descaling required · water inlet fault · convection fan · door seal · temperature sensor · control board · steam circuit blocked</div>
      </div>

      <div class="service-card">
        <div class="service-icon">🌿</div>
        <div class="service-name">Outdoor Grill Repair</div>
        <div class="service-desc">Wolf outdoor grills and outdoor kitchen equipment. LA's outdoor kitchens run year-round — and the combination of coastal salt air, Santa Ana wind, and daily use creates specific wear patterns. Ignition system corrosion, burner tube blockage, and temperature control failure are the most common issues we see on Wolf outdoor grills in LA.</div>
        <div class="service-issues">Common: ignition failure · burner tube blocked · temperature control · valve corrosion (coastal) · infrared burner · weatherproofing · rotisserie motor · sear burner</div>
      </div>
    </div>

    <div class="tip-block tip-outdoor" style="margin-top:32px">
      <div class="tip-label">🌿 Wolf Outdoor Kitchen — The Service Most Shops Skip</div>
      <div class="tip-text">LA outdoor kitchens run 12 months a year — and Wolf outdoor grills are exposed to conditions that indoor appliances never face. Salt air from the coast corrodes valve stems and ignition electrodes within 2–3 seasons if untreated. We service Wolf outdoor grills comprehensively: burner cleaning, ignition system, valve inspection, and weatherproofing. Most general appliance companies decline outdoor grill work. We specialize in it.</div>
    </div>
  </div>
</section>

<!-- 03 — THE SUITE -->
<section class="section section-black">
  <div class="section-inner">
    <div class="section-num">03 — The Kitchen Suite</div>
    <h2 class="section-title">Wolf + Sub-Zero + Cove — One Service Call</h2>
    <p class="section-lead">Wolf, Sub-Zero, and Cove are all owned by Sub-Zero Group. Many of the finest LA kitchens have all three. We service the complete suite — range, refrigerator, and dishwasher — in a single visit from one technician who knows all three brands.</p>

    <div class="suite-grid">
      <div class="suite-card featured">
        <div class="suite-brand">Wolf</div>
        <div class="suite-role">Cooking</div>
        <div class="suite-desc">Ranges, ovens, cooktops, steam ovens, ventilation, outdoor grills. Professional heat since 1934.</div>
      </div>
      <div class="suite-card">
        <div class="suite-brand">Sub-Zero</div>
        <div class="suite-role">Refrigeration</div>
        <div class="suite-desc">Built-in refrigerators, wine columns, freezer columns, undercounter units. Dual refrigeration since 1945.</div>
      </div>
      <div class="suite-card">
        <div class="suite-brand">Cove</div>
        <div class="suite-role">Dishwashing</div>
        <div class="suite-desc">The dishwasher designed specifically to pair with Wolf and Sub-Zero kitchens. We service all Cove models.</div>
      </div>
    </div>

    <div style="margin-top:40px">
      <div class="features-2col">
        <ul class="features-list">
          <li><strong>Dual-Stack Burner Technology</strong> — Wolf's dual-stack burner has two separate flame rings: an outer high-heat ring (up to 20,000 BTU) and an inner precision ring for simmering. When the igniter fails on a dual-stack, both rings are affected — and generic igniters don't fit the geometry. We carry model-specific OEM Wolf igniters.</li>
          <li><strong>Variable-Speed Convection Fan</strong> — Wolf's M Series ovens use a convection fan that adjusts speed automatically based on oven temperature and load. When the motor starts running at a single fixed speed, baking results become inconsistent. This is a motor or speed-controller failure — we diagnose precisely before replacing the assembly.</li>
          <li><strong>Infrared Broiler</strong> — Wolf's infrared broiler reaches 1,850°F — far hotter than standard electric broil elements. Infrared broiler failures look similar to standard element failures but require different diagnostic approach. We test the infrared element, the reflector, and the control circuit separately.</li>
          <li><strong>Ventilation Back-Pressure</strong> — A blocked or failed Wolf range hood doesn't just fail to ventilate — it creates back-pressure that can affect combustion on the burners below, causing irregular flame and incomplete ignition. We always check hood performance as part of range service calls.</li>
        </ul>
        <div>
          <div class="tip-block" style="background:#0a1a0a; border-color:#2a7a2a; margin-top:0">
            <div class="tip-label" style="color:#5abf5a">🌿 Outdoor Kitchen Integration</div>
            <div class="tip-text" style="color:#bbb">Wolf's outdoor cooking line — grills, side burners, griddles, and fryers — is designed as a permanent outdoor kitchen installation. LA homeowners use this equipment year-round, which means year-round wear. Salt air from the coast reaches outdoor kitchens in Malibu, Pacific Palisades, and Manhattan Beach within hours of installation. Annual weatherproofing and ignition service prevents the corrosion failures that sideline outdoor kitchens mid-season.</div>
          </div>
          <div class="tip-block tip-blue" style="margin-top:16px">
            <div class="tip-label">💧 Steam Oven + LA Hard Water</div>
            <div class="tip-text">Wolf's CSO steam ovens in LA need descaling 30–50% more often than Wolf's standard interval. At 300+ ppm, LA water accelerates steam generator scaling significantly. We set the descaling reminder to match your water hardness — not the factory default — every time we service a Wolf steam oven.</div>
          </div>
        </div>
      </div>
    </div>
  </div>
</section>

<!-- 04 — COMMON PROBLEMS -->
<section class="section">
  <div class="section-inner">
    <div class="section-num">04 — Common Problems</div>
    <h2 class="section-title">Most Common Wolf Failures in Los Angeles</h2>
    <p class="section-lead">Wolf appliances are built for professional use — they fail less often than consumer brands but in specific, well-documented ways. LA's climate adds its own signature.</p>

    <div class="problems-grid">
      <div class="problem-card">
        <div class="problem-title">🔥 Burner Igniter Failure</div>
        <div class="problem-cause">Coastal salt air corrodes Wolf igniter ceramics faster than inland properties. Grease contamination from high-heat cooking also cracks ceramics over time. Dual-stack igniters are geometry-specific — only OEM Wolf igniters fit correctly. We test each igniter individually and replace only what's failed.</div>
        <span class="problem-tag tag-common">Most Common</span>
      </div>

      <div class="problem-card">
        <div class="problem-title">🌡️ Oven Temperature Off or Fluctuating</div>
        <div class="problem-cause">Three causes in order of frequency: worn door gasket allowing heat loss, failing temperature probe, and convection fan running at reduced speed. We test all three before ordering parts. A door gasket fix costs a fraction of a probe replacement and resolves 40% of temperature calls.</div>
        <span class="problem-tag tag-common">Most Common</span>
      </div>

      <div class="problem-card">
        <div class="problem-title">💨 Hood Motor Failure</div>
        <div class="problem-cause">Wolf range hood blower motors run continuously during cooking — at high-output Wolf burner levels, the motors work hard. Failure usually starts as noise before the motor stops completely. We carry replacement blower assemblies for current Wolf hood models. A failed hood affects range performance — we check both together.</div>
        <span class="problem-tag tag-common">Most Common</span>
      </div>

      <div class="problem-card">
        <div class="problem-title">🌿 Outdoor Grill Won't Ignite</div>
        <div class="problem-cause">Salt air corrosion on the ignition electrodes or valve stems — the most common outdoor grill failure in coastal LA. The electrode tip corrodes and loses its spark gap. Replacement requires cleaning the burner tube simultaneously (spider nests and debris also block outdoor burners seasonally).</div>
        <span class="problem-tag tag-outdoor">Outdoor / Coastal</span>
      </div>

      <div class="problem-card">
        <div class="problem-title">☁️ Steam Oven Not Steaming</div>
        <div class="problem-cause">Scale buildup in the steam generator — accelerated by LA hard water. The standard Wolf descale program handles normal scale; heavy buildup from hard water requires a deeper service. We descale manually, test the water inlet valve (often seized simultaneously), and reset the descale interval.</div>
        <span class="problem-tag tag-la">LA Hard Water</span>
      </div>

      <div class="problem-card">
        <div class="problem-title">⚡ Induction Zone Dead</div>
        <div class="problem-cause">Single-zone inverter failure — the most common Wolf induction cooktop failure. One zone stops responding while others work normally. Wolf's induction architecture uses discrete inverters per zone, which means a single-zone failure is usually a zone inverter, not the main control board. We test by zone before recommending a full board replacement.</div>
        <span class="problem-tag tag-common">Most Common</span>
      </div>
    </div>
  </div>
</section>

